Singapore-flagged ship  the Dali  had a "momentary loss of propulsion" and was piloted when it collided with Baltimore's Francis Scott Key Bridge  said the Maritime and Port Authority of Singapore.https://str.sg/kzcm

Unfortunate incident which surely got the world media attention’s.Prior to this information of “momentary loss of propulsion”  was discussing this with another trader on what could be the effect on markets/counters. My thought was this happened due to either of the below 👇1) Human Negligence or2) Vessel MalfunctionNow  initial investigation is pointing towards Vessel Malfunction and the loss of control More unfortunately  this was a Singapore flagged vessel and thus Maritime Port Authority SG is also assisting on the investigations.Extract: The Maritime and Port Authority of Singapore (MPA) said in response to The Straits Times’ queries that it has contacted the US Coast Guard  the Office of Marine Safety and the National Transportation Safety Board to offer assistance as the flag administration  adding that investigators from Singapore’s Transport Safety Investigation Bureau and MPA are headed to Baltimore to support investigations.

🚀Pika World Markets Update - 27 March 2024🚀🥁Stocks faded towards the last hour of trading  which caught us a little off guard. Since then  we have pared off the positions  but now the pre-market is back up. This is how directionless the market is during a week of few essential economic calendars except for the PCE index on Friday  which falls on a public holiday when markets are closed.🎯As we look beyond this short trading week  it is useful to explore what's ahead. The job numbers for March and the March consumer price will be released on 10 April.🎲We can expect the FOMC minutes  too  and the European Central Bank policy decision.🎢Next  another earnings season will likely start on 12 April  with big banks leading the way. We are now expecting the robust earnings growth to cool from the 2023 level. Nonetheless  Pika World believes that the current per-share earnings for the S&P 500 are healthy  as they increased by 10% annually for the fourth quarter. This is double the expectation from many analysts weeks before the earnings results kept rolling in.💰For the first quarter of 2024  we expect earnings per share growth of around 5%  which would be a big step down but still constructive in an economy that faces many possible economic  political and social fabric headwinds.📪History shows that first-quarter results tend to be better  and if it holds or there's a significant beat to the earnings  we could see a whole new paradise in the equity market.Cheers Pika Nat.🧃
